  "root_text": {
    "sn7.6:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 7.6 ",
    "sn7.6:0.2": "1. Arahantavagga ",
    "sn7.6:0.3": "Jaṭāsutta ",
    "sn7.6:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn7.6:1.2": "Atha kho jaṭābhāradvājo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṁ sammodi. ",
    "sn7.6:1.3": "Sammodanīyaṁ kathaṁ sāraṇīyaṁ vītisāretvā ekamantaṁ nisīdi. ",
    "sn7.6:1.4": "Ekamantaṁ nisinno kho jaṭābhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn7.6:2.1": "“Antojaṭā bahijaṭā, ",
    "sn7.6:2.2": "Jaṭāya jaṭitā pajā; ",
    "sn7.6:2.3": "Taṁ taṁ gotama pucchāmi, ",
    "sn7.6:2.4": "Ko imaṁ vijaṭaye jaṭan”ti. ",
    "sn7.6:3.1": "“Sīle patiṭṭhāya naro sapañño, ",
    "sn7.6:3.2": "Cittaṁ paññañca bhāvayaṁ; ",
    "sn7.6:3.3": "Ātāpī nipako bhikkhu, ",
    "sn7.6:3.4": "So imaṁ vijaṭaye jaṭaṁ. ",
    "sn7.6:4.1": "Yesaṁ rāgo ca doso ca, ",
    "sn7.6:4.2": "avijjā ca virājitā; ",
    "sn7.6:4.3": "Khīṇāsavā arahanto, ",
    "sn7.6:4.4": "tesaṁ vijaṭitā jaṭā. ",
    "sn7.6:5.1": "Yattha nāmañca rūpañca, ",
    "sn7.6:5.2": "asesaṁ uparujjhati; ",
    "sn7.6:5.3": "Paṭighaṁ rūpasaññā ca, ",
    "sn7.6:5.4": "etthesā chijjate jaṭā”ti. ",
    "sn7.6:6.1": "Evaṁ vutte, jaṭābhāradvājo bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn7.6:6.2": "“abhikkantaṁ, bho gotama …pe… ",
    "sn7.6:6.3": "aññataro ca panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṁ ahosī”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn7.6:0.1": "Linked Discourses 7.6 ",
    "sn7.6:0.2": "1. The Perfected Ones ",
    "sn7.6:0.3": "With Bhāradvāja of the Matted Hair ",
    "sn7.6:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn7.6:1.2": "Then the brahmin Bhāradvāja of the Matted Hair went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. ",
    "sn7.6:1.3": "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, ",
    "sn7.6:1.4": "and addressed the Buddha in verse: ",
    "sn7.6:2.1": "“Tangled within, tangled without: ",
    "sn7.6:2.2": "these people are tangled in tangles. ",
    "sn7.6:2.3": "I ask you this, Gotama: ",
    "sn7.6:2.4": "who can untangle this tangle?” ",
    "sn7.6:3.1": "“A wise person grounded in ethics, ",
    "sn7.6:3.2": "developing the mind and wisdom, ",
    "sn7.6:3.3": "a keen and alert mendicant—",
    "sn7.6:3.4": "they can untangle this tangle. ",
    "sn7.6:4.1": "Those in whom greed, hate, and ignorance ",
    "sn7.6:4.2": "have faded away; ",
    "sn7.6:4.3": "the perfected ones with defilements ended—",
    "sn7.6:4.4": "they have untangled the tangle. ",
    "sn7.6:5.1": "Where name and form ",
    "sn7.6:5.2": "cease with nothing left over; ",
    "sn7.6:5.3": "as well as impingement and perception of form: ",
    "sn7.6:5.4": "it’s there that the tangle is cut.” ",
    "sn7.6:6.1": "When he had spoken, Bhāradvāja of the Matted Hair said to the Buddha, ",
    "sn7.6:6.2": "“Excellent, worthy Gotama! …” … ",
    "sn7.6:6.3": "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected. "
  },
